INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES(43, 78, 18, 'Anybody got a truck and some spare time this week? For real.', 'Okay, first off, our stuff is still on hold safe and sound at Jeune Lune after a royal pillaging of the space by the city of Minneapolis last weekend. Secondly, my friend Kelly, who to date, has been an absolute peach, has reached her point of ripeness and made a clear request of me today to have all items out of the space by week''s end (Nov 22).\r\n\r\nSeems a lot of people have been "special-requesting-her-to-death" and a combination of an 80 hour work week last week and a desire to take some time off next week have created a somewhat surprising bump in our road. Nevertheless, this is what we have to deal with. And here''s catch number 2: she needs us to pick the stuff up during business hours.\r\n\r\nSo (deep breath) here is what I propose and what I would like your blessing to move ahead with...\r\n\r\nSince it seems highly unlikely that our group will be able to collectively take a day off work with short notice, I''ve been trolling craigslist in hopes of finding two guys with a truck who are available this week. I''m thinking the cost of this will run approximately\r\n$100-200 and I would work very hard to keep it on the low end of cost. I would then be able to meet the movers there and shepherd them back to the Soap Factory. I would also front payment, to be reimbursed later. We can then mail the check for payment of goods to Kelly as soon as they are available.\r\n\r\nSo here are my questions to you:\r\n\r\nIs there another option for moving these materials from the space that any of you can come up with that might be more feasible?\r\n\r\nShould we move ahead with my proposal is this possible for our budget?\r\n\r\nAre we any closer with space information at the Soap Factory?\r\n\r\nDoes anyone have any leads on people with trucks that I might be able to call?\r\n\r\nThanks in advance for your quick response to these requests given our time restraints for our lovely lovely materials.', 'Okay, first off, our stuff is still on hold safe and sound at Jeune Lune after a royal pillaging of the space by the city of Minneapolis last weekend. Secondly, my friend Kelly, who to date, has been an absolute peach, has reached her point of ripeness and made a clear request of me today to have all items out of the space by week''s end (Nov 22).\r\n\r', '', 1226981881, 1);
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES(44, 79, 18, 'Volunteers needed Saturday between 11 am and 12 pm', 'Jaime and I had a heroic day of moving stuff from Jeune Lune to the Soap Factory with our friendly and capable laborers. We did our best (and truly a lot of materials were moved) but were not able to finish the job, mostly due to the Soap Factory gallery opening and us getting kicked out. \r\n\r\nA truck rental may yet again be required to remove the remaining items but if we get volunteers we can save the money we spent on the extra labor today. Money spent to date: $100 for transportation, $150 for materials.\r\n\r\nJaime and I are both busy on Saturday and will not be able to assist with this last load of stuff. So I ask the group: who is bold and brave and willing to make this last push to move items from one space to another less than two miles away? Someone needs to rent the truck (see earlier post for Reddy-Rents as a resource)and many hands are needed to move materials. \r\n\r\nThe Saturday time, from 11 am to 12 pm, is our only opportunity to pick these items up. This hour is a special favor granted just for us. I do not get the feeling the window is flexible. \r\n\r\nItems to be picked up include:\r\n\r\nIn the woodshop:\r\n1 bench 8'' long\r\n2'' x 8'' platform\r\nred veneer pieces(on the bench)\r\nstyrofoam board\r\n\r\nIn the basement: \r\n2 8'' x 4'' platforms (original location)\r\n1 platform with wheels attached on bottom (adjoining room)\r\n\r\nIn the hallway by the elevator - Main Floor:\r\nCart loaded with 8'' x 4'' (mostly) plywood and press board. Probably 10-15 pieces minimum.\r\nPlease note: Cart belongs to Jeune Lune\r\n\r\nMaterials that are left in the space will become forfeit after this week. If there is any way that we can get these materials it would be a great help to the project. \r\n\r\nI anticipate approximately a 1 and a 1/2 hour time commitment to complete the project (a little more for the person procuring the vehicle. \r\n\r\nItems moved to the Soap Factory must be added to the stacks of other material at the base of the stairs in the Soap Factory basement. Soap Factory will be doing cleaning of that space this weekend, so it is imperative that all of our items are clearly marked and thus, not removed.\r\n\r\nIt is worth noting that Ben, at Soap Factory, was very firm about us needing to be done unloading materials by the time business opened for the gallery, The gallery opens at noon on Saturday. This gives a small window of time for pick up and unloading. Challenging, but not impossible. \r\n\r\nI''m very willing to talk over scenarios with anyone who might be interested. Jaime would also be a good resource and of course Lesley or Emily. \r\n\r\nBut please, if you do have some time, it would be a great help.\r\n\r\nThanks - Andrea\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Jaime and I had a heroic day of moving stuff from Jeune Lune to the Soap Factory with our friendly and capable laborers. We did our best (and truly a lot of materials were moved) but were not able to finish the job, mostly due to the Soap Factory gallery opening and us getting kicked out. \r\n\r\nA truck rental may yet again be required to remove the remaining items but if we get volunteers we can save the money we spent on the extra labor today. Money spent to date: $100 for transportation, $150 for materials.\r\n\r', '', 1227221453, 1);
